<p>Where the code diverges from the paper. The official implementation is production-quality and largely faithful, but two details matter. First, segmentation is driven by gripper or hand command flips; the code also contains a smoothed end-effector pose and an xyz sign-flip helper, but that helper is dead code in both modes. Second, Stage-A weights are mean-normalized within the primitive term and within the transition term, not divided by <latex>|\mathcal{P}|</latex> as Eq. 12 states. Because the number of primitives and transitions differs, this changes the relative scale of the two terms. The paper's ablation says transitions matter more than primitives; that result should be revisited with the exact paper normalization. I preserved patches for both issues in the thread.</p>

